Arctic Monkeys postpone appearance in Glasgow because of the illness Alex Turners
The skirt band Arctic Monkeys postponed an appearance in Glasgow after their Leadsänger fell with laryngitis ill.
The band from Sheffield should play on Friday in the Hydro.
Because of the illness of the Leadsängers Alex Turner the concert must be brought out now, however.
The announcement of the band came after she had to postpone before already an appearance in the LG Arena in Birmingham on Thursday.
In a declaration on their official web site the Arctic Monkeys informed: „According to the decision, to call off the show in the LG Arena in Birmingham this evening as well as on medical advice must the Arctic Monkeys also the show in the Hydro in Glasgow on Friday to which call off 1st November."
„With Alex Turner a laryngitis was diagnosed, for which it cannot occur unfortunately."
The show in the LG Arena in Birmingham occurs now on 20th November, that in the Hydro in Glasgow was brought out on the 21st November.
All tickets retain validity for these shows.
We apologize to all ticket holders for the inconveniences arisen from that.
Please turn to the customer service at the sales offices at which you bought your ticket if you need further support.
